caption.center: JACK HAROLD ROBB, JR., APPELLANT v. ALICIA GWENDOLYN ROBB, APPELLEE

court.center: Court of Appeals of Texas, Second District, Fort Worth.

opinion.posture: Appealed from the 231st District Court of Tarrant County.
opinion.panel: PANEL: GARDNER, WALKER, and MCCOY, JJ.
opinion.opinion_text:
We have considered "Appellant's Motion For Voluntary Dismissal." It is the court's opinion that the motion should be granted; therefore, we dismiss the appeal. See Tex. R. App. P. 42.1(a)(1), 43.2(f).
Costs of the appeal shall be paid by appellant, for which let execution issue. See Tex. R. App. P. 43.4.
